Build succeeds. Here's what was created:

**3 files added:**

1. **`Components/ScreenSize.cs`** — enum with `Mobile`, `Tablet`, `Desktop` values
2. **`Components/ScreenSizeProvider.razor`** — wraps `ChildContent` in a `<CascadingValue>`, uses JS interop to listen for `resize` events, categorizes the viewport width, and updates the cascading value. Defaults to `Desktop`.
3. **`wwwroot/screenSizeInterop.js`** — JS module that sends `window.innerWidth` on load and on every resize

**Usage in child components:**

```razor
@code {
    [CascadingParameter]
    public ScreenSize ScreenSize { get; set; }
}
```

The component must be rendered with interactive server mode (which your app already uses) so JS interop is available. It cleans up the resize listener on disposal.
